This repository is primarily intended for educational purposes. Students and 
educators are encouraged to:

✅ Use the materials for learning and teaching Python programming
✅ Modify examples and exercises for educational enhancement
✅ Share knowledge and collaborate on improvements
✅ Build upon the concepts for personal and academic projects

Please note:
- When using materials in academic settings, proper attribution is appreciated
- Commercial use of the educational content should acknowledge the source
- Contributions and improvements to the course materials are welcome

